Nigerian singer, Davido has told a really story of how he managed to get Nas to record a verse on his album, A Better Time.  Davido told the story during an interview on BBC Radio 1xtra. According to him, he was in Los Angeles recording when he decided to visit the bathroom and while washing his hands, he looked to his side and saw Nas right there beside him. They exchanged greetings and Davido returned to the studio. However, while he was doing his thing, recording and singing, he looked back and saw that Nas was there with them in the same studio. It was at this time that he asked Nas if he could drop a verse on the album and Nas agreed. Watch the video below: David Adedeji Adeleke, better known by his stage name Davido, is a Nigerian singer, songwriter, and record producer. He was born in Atlanta and raised in Lagos. Davido made his music debut as a member of the music group KB International. He studied business administration at Oakwood University before dropping… October 27, 2019 In "Features" 5 years after making his industry breakthrough, Tekno Miles is finally set to release his debut solo album. If the message shared on his Instagram page is anything to go by, then we may not have not wait for long for the debut album of the talented singer/producer, Tekno. Teasing… July 13, 2018 In "Entertainment" Popular Nigerian singer, Davido finally drops the tracklist of his highly-anticipated album, “A Good Time”. “Blow my mind” which Chris Brown was featured in, was also seen on the album. Davido revealed “A Good Time” is scheduled for release on November 22 via Davido Music Worldwide/Sony Music U.K./RCA Records. He… November 22, 2019 In "Entertainment"